// SndSequence (SNDSEQ) is a script section that defines sequences of 
// sounds to play in order, allowing complex sound patterns or variations 
// for actions and events.

// https://zdoom.org/w/index.php?title=SNDSEQ

// Non-UDMF way, place the 'SoundSequence' thing in the map door/platform sector
// and set the index number in the arg index.

// With UDMF, apply the name identifier in the sector 'other properties', 
// no need to place any thing in the map. 

:DoorTemplateSoundSequence
	
	door 1	// Type and index number
	
	volume 100							// Initial volume
	playloop SFX/SwitchTemplateOn 	20	// Loop until the door fully open (time in TICS)
	stopsound SFX/SwitchTemplateOff		// Play one time in the end
end

:PlatformTemplateSoundSequence
	
	platform 1
	
	volume 100
	playloop SFX/SwitchTemplateOff 	15
	stopsound SFX/SwitchTemplateOn
end